WEBVTT

00:00.078 --> 00:02.952
Previously on AMC's
"Better Call Saul"...

00:02.977 --> 00:05.218
Free. I'll shoot the spot for free.

00:05.243 --> 00:06.310
For free?

00:06.335 --> 00:07.947
You're losing money.

00:07.949 --> 00:09.115
My brother is sick.

00:09.117 --> 00:11.150
He's making mistakes with his clients.

00:11.152 --> 00:12.785
You're not gonna do anything, are you?

00:12.787 --> 00:14.195
To new beginnings.

00:14.220 --> 00:16.789
I need to see Dr. Cruz
as soon as possible.

00:16.791 --> 00:18.828
The man killed for
helping the truck driver.

00:18.853 --> 00:21.444
You are trying to correct
something which cannot be corrected.

00:21.469 --> 00:23.297
Hector wants to use my dad's business.

00:23.322 --> 00:26.423
If you manage to pull this
off and switch those pills,

00:26.448 --> 00:27.733
switch them back.

00:27.735 --> 00:30.159
I'm gonna need one more thing from you.

00:32.000 --> 00:38.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:51.743 --> 00:53.743
Let there be light.

00:53.746 --> 00:56.180
And then there was light.

00:59.517 --> 01:02.182
Geez. Will you look at this...

01:06.459 --> 01:09.263
That's where your mom used to work.

01:09.288 --> 01:11.327
Right back there, doin' the books.

01:11.352 --> 01:13.062
Yeah. Whatever.

01:17.827 --> 01:19.935
Hey, remember when we
used to ditch fourth,

01:19.960 --> 01:21.405
come in the back door?

01:21.407 --> 01:23.734
Tell your folks it was a free period.

01:23.759 --> 01:25.646
O'Dell's Algebra Two.

01:25.671 --> 01:27.421
Mr. O'Dell.

01:27.446 --> 01:29.680
Man, that guy was a butthole.

01:29.682 --> 01:32.149
And your mom, you know, I
think she knew we were skipping,

01:32.151 --> 01:33.680
but she'd always stop what she was doing

01:33.704 --> 01:35.409
and gimme a pack of Little Debbie's.

01:35.434 --> 01:38.989
Ahh. Think all those Little
Debbie's put them out of business.

01:40.305 --> 01:42.280
Hey, how'd you get up
there when you were a kid?

01:42.282 --> 01:44.811
Couple of milk crates, you know?

01:47.888 --> 01:49.721
Ohh.

01:57.364 --> 01:58.930
All right.

02:01.935 --> 02:05.180
No. No. No. Nope.

02:05.205 --> 02:06.510
Ah.

02:08.232 --> 02:09.556
Boom.

02:09.580 --> 02:11.363
Indian Head penny.

02:11.388 --> 02:13.378
All right? That's
worth about three bucks.

02:13.380 --> 02:15.697
We polish it up, run the coin game...

02:15.722 --> 02:17.815
Nice. We get 150 bucks, easy.

02:17.817 --> 02:20.762
$150? We got a $110 for a
plain vanilla half dollar.

02:20.787 --> 02:22.787
This... this is actually rare.

02:22.789 --> 02:24.360
I mean, you can see it.

02:24.407 --> 02:26.891
- $300, easy.
- Oh, $300?

02:26.893 --> 02:29.069
Me likey. Yeah.

02:29.094 --> 02:32.633
Now you're gonna tell me what your
coin collection was doin' up there.

02:32.658 --> 02:34.157
Uh...

02:35.477 --> 02:37.571
It's a long story.

02:37.596 --> 02:41.606
Um... let's get outta here.

02:52.805 --> 02:56.254
- All right. Now. Let's hit it.
- No, there might be another one.

02:56.256 --> 02:57.622
All right.

02:57.624 --> 02:58.856
Then give.

02:58.858 --> 03:01.086
What's the deal with the coins?

03:05.031 --> 03:06.422
Well, uh...

03:07.830 --> 03:11.116
I was what? Uh, 12 or so?

03:11.141 --> 03:12.604
I was working the register.

03:12.606 --> 03:15.840
Guy comes in, buys a box of Ivory Flakes

03:15.842 --> 03:19.711
and a sixer of Old Style.

03:21.563 --> 03:24.872
He pays with a couple bucks and...

03:25.352 --> 03:26.618
this.

03:26.620 --> 03:29.053
The second I see it,
I know what it is...

03:29.055 --> 03:31.456
it's a George Washington silver.

03:31.458 --> 03:34.459
I tell my dad, "Pop,
this quarter is rare.

03:34.484 --> 03:37.458
It's worth four bucks."

03:37.872 --> 03:39.397
Barely get the words outta my mouth...

03:39.422 --> 03:42.544
he hightails it outta
here to give it back.

03:42.569 --> 03:43.927
He can't find the guy,

03:43.952 --> 03:46.070
so he tapes it to the
side of the register...

03:46.072 --> 03:47.648
he's hoping...

03:47.673 --> 03:49.695
that this guy will come back...

03:49.720 --> 03:52.076
so we can return it.

03:52.078 --> 03:54.078
After about a week,
he starts talking about

03:54.080 --> 03:56.314
givin' it to Father
Mahoney for the poor box,

03:56.316 --> 03:58.060
so I make it disappear.

03:58.085 --> 04:00.685
And after that, every day after
school, I'm checking the till.

04:00.710 --> 04:02.069
You know, something catches my eye,

04:02.093 --> 04:05.323
I stick it in the box, put
it up there for good luck.

04:06.693 --> 04:08.860
So much for good luck.

04:10.389 --> 04:13.427
It was a cryin' shame
they lost this place.

04:13.452 --> 04:16.255
They never shoulda bought
it in the first place.

04:16.279 --> 04:18.779
My dad didn't have it in him.

04:18.805 --> 04:20.137
Whaddya mean?

04:20.163 --> 04:22.240
Your folks worked so hard.

04:22.242 --> 04:23.468
Yeah, they worked hard!

04:23.493 --> 04:26.310
They worked a lotta
hours for a lotta years.

04:26.335 --> 04:27.638
For nothin'.

04:27.663 --> 04:30.864
I dunno, Jimmy. He had a lotta
customers. Everybody liked him.

04:30.866 --> 04:34.232
Everybody liked him
'cause he was a soft touch.

04:34.257 --> 04:37.237
You know? Every deadbeat in
the neighborhood owed him money.

04:37.239 --> 04:38.872
You come in here with a sob story,

04:38.874 --> 04:41.675
you leave with a pat on the
back and a gallon of milk.

04:41.677 --> 04:43.276
He... he coulda made it work.

04:43.278 --> 04:45.078
He coulda sold beer and cigarettes

04:45.080 --> 04:46.880
to the kids from Mary-Margaret's,

04:46.882 --> 04:50.382
but... oh, no, not him.

04:50.407 --> 04:53.717
He was never gonna do what he had to do.

05:03.998 --> 05:05.866
How'd you know there'd be another?

05:10.357 --> 05:11.757
Oh.

05:11.782 --> 05:13.749
Banquet's over.

05:14.576 --> 05:18.077
Those conventioneers been
talking farm equipment

05:18.102 --> 05:20.236
for 10 hours straight...

05:20.261 --> 05:22.349
now they wanna party.

05:23.919 --> 05:26.919
Gonna be a big night,
my friend. Whaddya say?

05:26.944 --> 05:29.336
- Time to get moving?
- Let's go.

